# Supply Chain Shock Simulation

A Deep Reinforcement Learning framework for training autonomous supply chain agents that maintain stability under catastrophic disruptions.

## Architecture

```
DRL Agent(s) ──actions──▶ SimPy DES Engine ──state/reward──▶ DRL Agent(s)
                              ▲
                              │
                    Shock Injector (demand surges,
                    supplier outages, logistics delays)
```

**Key Components:**
- **SimPy DES Engine** — Stochastic demand, lead times, and resource contention
- **Shock Injector** — 5 disruption types with probabilistic and deterministic triggering
- **Composite Reward** — 6-term function with anti-Bullwhip stability penalty
- **Heuristic Baselines** — Base-Stock, (s,S), Beer Game policies for benchmarking

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run tests
pytest tests/ -v

# Train the agent (500K steps, ~10 min on CPU)
python scripts/train.py

# Evaluate against baselines
python scripts/evaluate.py --model outputs/models/final_model.zip

# Monitor training
tensorboard --logdir outputs/logs
```

## Project Structure

```
├── configs/
│   ├── default.yaml          # Environment, reward, training hyperparameters
│   └── shocks.yaml           # Shock catalog and scenario presets
├── src/
│   ├── environment/
│   │   ├── des_engine.py     # Core SimPy simulation
│   │   ├── supply_chain_env.py  # Gymnasium wrapper
│   │   └── shock_injector.py    # Disruption event manager
│   ├── agents/
│   │   ├── single_agent.py   # PPO trainer (Stable Baselines3)
│   │   └── heuristic_baselines.py  # Classical policies
│   ├── rewards/
│   │   └── composite_reward.py  # Multi-term reward function
│   ├── scenarios/
│   │   └── monte_carlo.py    # What-if scenario analysis
│   └── utils/
│       ├── config_loader.py  # YAML config parser
│       └── visualization.py  # Analysis plots
├── scripts/
│   ├── train.py              # Training entry point
│   └── evaluate.py           # Evaluation entry point
└── tests/
    ├── test_env.py
    ├── test_shocks.py
    └── test_reward.py
```

## Scenario Presets

Run deterministic shock scenarios:

```bash
# No shocks (baseline)
python scripts/train.py --shock-mode deterministic --scenario calm

# Supplier outage then demand surge
python scripts/train.py --shock-mode deterministic --scenario cascading_crisis

# All shocks at 3x probability
python scripts/train.py --shock-mode stochastic --scenario worst_case
```
